════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section style="background:var(--color-base, #f2ead4); padding:80px 24px;">
  <div style="max-width:800px; margin:0 auto;">
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.75rem; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:0.15em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#b98229; margin-bottom:1rem;">Local Expertise</p>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:clamp(1.8rem, 3.5vw, 2.8rem); font-weight:400; font-variation-settings:'opsz' 32; line-height:1.2; color:#191817; margin-bottom:1.75rem;">Rail access and genuine value on the south-west corridor.</h2>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      Oxley offers the south-western corridor's rail commute advantage at an entry price that buyers priced out of Corinda, Sherwood and Graceville still consider seriously. Oxley Station on the Ipswich/Springfield line is the suburb's defining asset, and the established housing stock on reasonable blocks has consistently attracted families and investors who understand the value proposition.
    </p>
<!-- APPRAISAL FORM -->
