<section style="background:var(--color-base, #f2ead4); padding:40px 24px 80px;">
  <div style="max-width:800px; margin:0 auto;">
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.75rem; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:0.15em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#b98229; margin-bottom:1rem;">FAQ</p>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:clamp(1.8rem, 3.5vw, 2.8rem); font-weight:400; font-variation-settings:'opsz' 32; line-height:1.2; color:#191817; margin-bottom:2.5rem;">Common questions about Oxley.</h2>
    <div style="display:flex; flex-direction:column;">

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          What drives property values in Oxley?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Oxley property values are driven primarily by rail access at Oxley Station, proximity to Corinda and Sherwood, block size and renovation potential of the 1950s-to-1970s housing stock. Properties within comfortable walking distance of the station attract a materially wider buyer pool than those requiring a car connection to public transport.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          How long does it take to sell a home in Oxley?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Well-priced Oxley homes typically sell within 28 to 45 days. Station-adjacent properties at the right price sell at the faster end of that range. Homes on busier roads or with larger renovation requirements tend to take closer to 45 days as the buyer pool is more selective.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          What is the lifestyle like in Oxley?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Oxley has an established, family-oriented suburb feel with Oxley Creek providing greenway character to the area. The rail line gives residents a genuine commute advantage, and the proximity to Corinda, Sherwood and Graceville means access to established shopping strips and services without the premium pricing of those addresses.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          Is Oxley a good entry point into the south-west corridor?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Yes. Oxley sits below Corinda and Sherwood in price but shares rail access and the established family character of that corridor. For buyers who want the south-west corridor's commute and community without the Sherwood premium, Oxley represents genuine value and strong long-term growth potential as those neighbouring suburbs continue to tighten.</p>
      </details>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

